        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 7:04PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brownfield. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brownfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
